formattedAddress: Ray Emery Dr. (Off George Bolt Memorial Dr.)

tip.text: Beef salad was yummy
Fresh fruits and a juicer available at breakfast! Also the staff went round with 3 types of tasting-portion smoothies for guests to choose from. Fresh coffee is made upon request. Good service.

venue.name: Aria Restaurant at Crowne Plaza Auckland

tip.text: Nutella spread bagel was a great snack. Served warm.
Delicious platter. A must have with bread and wine. Beautiful event space at the back for special occasions. Young wines served, quite a few sold out, exclusive to Poppies and not sold anywhere else.

formattedAddress: 25 Taranaki St, Te Aro (btw Courtenay Place and Wakefield)

tip.text: Cafe upstairs. Store is well stocked with cards, gifts and games. Love the wide selection.
Delicious Szechuan dumplings - generously packed with meat in a flavorful oily sauce. All day dimsum available. Full house on weekends so be sure to make reservation!
Roast meats, mapo tofu and salt and pepper squid are a must. This place draws a good crowd so be prepared to wait.

formattedAddress: 39a Courtenay Place (Btw Kent Tce & Tory St)

tip.text: Family friendly. Decent platter and steak. Good service, staff was short handed but very apologetic. Overall a good experience.
Combination dried noodles comes with a generous portion of fresh veg at the bottom.
Iced coffee comes with a huge chocolate fish and a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Great as a dessert actually.
Superb chicken wings and roast pork. Overall good standard and variety. Gets crowded on Sundays so be prepared to wait. Would definitely go back for seconds.
Superb variety of cakes and tea time snacks. Vegan Chocolate raspberry cake was delicious
Decent cheese and rocket scones. Coffee is rather sour if you like it that way but not for me.

venue.name: Red Rabbit Coffee Co. / Leeds Street Bakery
Red Rabbit Coffee Co. / Leeds Street Bakery

tip.text: Generous portion of ribs all for £12.50.
Curries are generally good. Poppadum comes with side sauces that pair really well.
Good fruit smoothies. Wraps are ok. Slightly dark if you sit deeper in the cafe.
Nice to sit by the windows while you kill time. Friendly staff.
Delightful cockles (so fresh!) and great shrimp paste chicken, tofu, salted egg prawns and spare ribs. Chili crabs a disappointment - not fresh and gravy was slightly watery with no kick.
3rd bus stop from heathrow terminals 2 &3. Double room is quite spacious. Great for a night's stay if you've time to kill before a flight. Small convenience store located in the hotel, free wifi
Decent full breakfasts if you're starving. Wifi password changes daily. Huge seating area upstairs. Does get crowded at lunch.
Newly opened (July 2016). Don't go for the chicken teriyaki noodles. Chicken has an odd marinade and is dry.
Good service and yummy food. Wide selection. 10% discount for flight crew. A five minute walk from Heathrow Hotel (Bath Rd).
Decent breakfast. Large seating area upstairs, free wifi
Shark cartilage soup was hearty and absolutely wonderful. Interestingly presented.

formattedAddress: Singapore Island Country Club (Island Club Rd)

tip.text: Get the mixed sashimi platter. Absolutely divine!
Tuna/salmon sushi is lovely!

formattedAddress: G/F Clarke Quay Central (6 Eu Tong Sen Street)

tip.text: Food has always been consistently good, despite peak times like CNY. Go for the steamed pomfret

venue.name: Chin Lee Restaurant 深利美食馆

tip.text: Fresh oysters are highly recommended. They're creamy and you can barely taste the strong fishiness that often comes with it. Pair with hot sauce! Chowder is slightly too heavy on cream.
Very average
My tiramisu ice cream was coated with cocoa powder- amazing! One of the best gelatos I've had.
Delicious spicy tuna rolls, reasonably priced too!
Tuna kimchi soup is a must. Chilli pork wasn't much to shout about- stone plate wasn't hot so the cabbage below wasn't cooking. Small eatery but decent food overall.
No nonsense cappuccino! Bold coffee from Shakey Isles coffee beans. Great industrial vibe in this hidden gem.
Fish & chips were alright. Decent battered scallops. 50cents for a small portion of ketchup or $2.50 for a larger pot. Otherwise no other sauces provided.
Amazing blackened beef salad. Meat was tender and went absolutely well with salad and dressing
Pork ribs were delicious and tender to the right degree. Sesame chicken was nicely fried before the braise. Perfect meal on a rainy day.

venue.name: Old Tiong Bahru Bak Kut Teh

tip.text: Good coffee and well put together desserts.
Prawn paste chicken is great. Kailan and tofu were salty and drenched in starch and oil.

venue.name: Holland Village XO Fish Head Bee Hun Restaurant

tip.text: Great view of the port.
Great place to spend the afternoon with wine, bread and cheese.
Surf and turf is value for money. Steak was perfectly done. As with the crispy fries. Salt and pepper squid were a delight - made from fresh, not frozen squid.
Quesadillas and cocktails are lovely. Served by a bubbly waitress - excellent service. Wonderful atmosphere!
Amazing mixed salad meal (chicken, lamb and beef) with a perfect combination of vegetables.  Worth every penny.
Simple dishes but done well. Shaved celery with sashimi is a very clever combination- takes away any fishy aftertaste
Delicious steak. Absolutely well done.
Juicy pork belly croissant and yakult sake were lovely.
Disappointing braised duck for a teochew restaurant. But radish kwayteow was delicious, so was the jelly pork.
